cs.EM, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with the analysis, design, and optimization of electromagnetic nanostructures using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.EM (Electromagnetism). The paper also uses autoencoder techniques for dimensionality reduction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves image processing and computer vision techniques for analyzing the electromagnetic responses of nanostructures, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also uses neural networks for solving the design problem, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the fabrication of nanostructures, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
